              <th scope="col">Application</th>
              <th scope="col">Rate</th>
              <th scope="col">Fidelity</th>
              <th scope="col">Reach</th>
              <th scope="col">Deployment</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">QKD</th>
              <td>kbit/s–Mbit/s key rates</td>
              <td>Modest (~0.85 raw)</td>
              <td>Metro to satellite</td>
              <td>Commercial, fielded</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">Distributed QC</th>
              <td>Per-gate Bell pairs</td>
              <td>High (≥0.99)</td>
              <td>Datacentre to metro</td>
              <td>Research / early proto</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">Blind QC</th>
              <td>Per-computation</td>
              <td>High (≥0.99)</td>
              <td>Client-to-server, any</td>
              <td>Research</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">Networked sensing</th>
              <td>Application-specific</td>
              <td>Protocol-specific</td>
              <td>City to global</td>
              <td>Research</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">Position verification</th>
              <td>Per-challenge single qubits</td>
              <td>Loss-tolerant constructions exist</td>
              <td>Light-time bounded geometry</td>
              <td>Theory + early photonic experiments</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">Multiparty consensus</th>
              <td>Per-decision (modest)</td>
              <td>High (security tightens with raw fidelity)</td>
              <td>Three or more endpoints; metro to inter-DC</td>
              <td>Theory + three-party photonic demos</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>
          The metrics subject covers what these demands mean for a network's engineering
          budget; the maturity subject covers where each application sits on the TRL
          ladder <SourceNote id="cacciapuoti-ieeetc-2020" />.
        </p>
      </section>

    </Stack>
  </Center>
</Infographic>

